1
00:00:00,078 --> 00:00:05,796
RECORD OF YOUTH

2
00:00:05,882 --> 00:00:07,358
THIS PROGRAM HAS BEEN SELECTED AS AN
"EXCELLENT BROADCAST CONTENT" AND IS SUPPORTED

3
00:00:07,452 --> 00:00:09,045
BY THE MINISTRY OF CULTURE, SPORTS, TOURISM
AND THE KOREA CREATIVE CONTENT AGENCY

4
00:00:09,561 --> 00:00:13,232
JI-A

5
00:00:22,908 --> 00:00:23,867
Hey.

6
00:00:23,951 --> 00:00:26,787
<i>I met with a reporter today.
You'll see an article about it.</i>

7
00:00:29,164 --> 00:00:30,082
What do you mean?

8
00:00:30,165 --> 00:00:31,834
Ji-a came to see me.

9
00:00:41,552 --> 00:00:42,928
I'm not following.

10
00:00:43,012 --> 00:00:44,847
This moody, selfish girl

11
00:00:44,930 --> 00:00:47,224
chose to make a little sacrifice for you.

12
00:00:47,307 --> 00:00:49,309
Hae-hyo is here. Let me talk to him first.

13
00:00:52,312 --> 00:00:53,605
Ji-a is one thing,

14
00:00:54,189 --> 00:00:56,817
but shouldn't you have told me
before she met the reporter?

15
00:00:56,900 --> 00:00:58,736
-That's why I'm here.
-You came too late.

16
00:01:00,904 --> 00:01:02,156
Are you mad at me?

17
00:01:04,783 --> 00:01:06,702
I wanted to help you.

18
00:01:06,785 --> 00:01:09,538
I cooperated because I thought
it'd be helpful for you.

19
00:01:10,664 --> 00:01:13,417
-Is that so wrong?
-With some help, you must refuse it.

20
00:01:13,500 --> 00:01:15,461
That's the case with Ji-a's help.

21
00:01:16,378 --> 00:01:17,254
You've changed.

22
00:01:18,422 --> 00:01:20,841
-How?
-The Sa Hye-jun I used to know

23
00:01:20,924 --> 00:01:23,886
would have been grateful to the people
who are trying to help him.

24
00:01:23,969 --> 00:01:26,805
Don't you see that I'm upset
because I'm grateful?

25
00:01:28,015 --> 00:01:30,392
I don't want to have to make lame excuses.

26
00:01:32,853 --> 00:01:35,939
The truth will come out with time,
so I just need to hold this out.

27
00:01:36,023 --> 00:01:39,109
I'm offering to make those lame excuses
on your behalf.

28
00:01:39,610 --> 00:01:41,945
You'd step in and help
if I were in this situation.

29
00:01:42,029 --> 00:01:43,322
The old you would have.

30
00:01:43,405 --> 00:01:45,741
Why do you keep saying that I've changed?

31
00:01:45,824 --> 00:01:48,035
Look at yourself.
You never used to be like this.

32
00:01:48,118 --> 00:01:50,621
You always respected my opinion
and consulted me first.

33
00:01:50,704 --> 00:01:53,082
You no longer have time for that.

34
00:01:53,165 --> 00:01:54,625
You're always busy.

35
00:01:54,708 --> 00:01:57,127
You're with Jeong-ha when you're free.
You don't have time for us.

36
00:01:58,420 --> 00:02:00,422
And Jin-u is dating Hae-na.

37
00:02:00,506 --> 00:02:02,049
What is this mess?

38
00:02:09,181 --> 00:02:10,307
Jin-u and Hae-na…

39
00:02:11,266 --> 00:02:12,559
When did you find out?

40
00:02:15,687 --> 00:02:16,688
So,

41
00:02:18,232 --> 00:02:19,566
you knew?

42
00:02:26,156 --> 00:02:27,908
Those jerks…

43
00:02:27,991 --> 00:02:29,409
You guys hid it from me?

44
00:02:31,620 --> 00:02:33,080
You guys fooled me?

45
00:02:33,163 --> 00:02:35,791
No. Just until Jin-u could tell you
himself…

46
00:02:45,384 --> 00:02:46,885
What's with him?

47
00:02:46,969 --> 00:02:48,929
I'm the one who should be angry now.

48
00:02:50,097 --> 00:02:52,850
I guess guys fight just like girls do.

49
00:02:53,934 --> 00:02:55,727
Don't guys tussle?

50
00:02:55,811 --> 00:02:57,563
You two are such gentlemen.

51
00:02:58,355 --> 00:03:00,774
In movies, I always see guys
punching each other.

52
00:03:06,780 --> 00:03:09,491
Anyway, you should thank Ji-a

53
00:03:09,575 --> 00:03:10,701
when you see her later.

54
00:03:11,201 --> 00:03:14,121
I'm so grateful that she stepped in.

55
00:03:16,039 --> 00:03:18,542
What did Hae-hyo and Ji-a talk about?

56
00:03:19,851 --> 00:03:26,403
RECORD OF YOUTH

57
00:03:26,508 --> 00:03:28,051
This isn't like you.

58
00:03:28,135 --> 00:03:29,970
Your parents won't be happy about this.

59
00:03:30,053 --> 00:03:32,097
Do you still like Hye-jun's girlfriend?

60
00:03:37,686 --> 00:03:39,479
Learn to hide your emotions,

61
00:03:39,563 --> 00:03:41,481
or Hye-jun will figure it out soon.

62
00:03:42,024 --> 00:03:43,859
If he finds out, he'll be so hurt.

63
00:03:44,443 --> 00:03:47,070
You know exactly where to poke.

64
00:03:47,154 --> 00:03:48,864
You'll be a great lawyer.

65
00:03:50,574 --> 00:03:52,492
I want to protect Hye-jun.

66
00:03:52,576 --> 00:03:54,077
When we were together,

67
00:03:54,161 --> 00:03:57,206
I did all sorts of things
to test him as well as my love.

68
00:03:57,289 --> 00:03:58,373
He's the real deal.

69
00:03:58,874 --> 00:04:00,292
That's my conclusion.

70
00:04:01,376 --> 00:04:04,588
And now that he's taken,

71
00:04:04,671 --> 00:04:06,089
I want him even more.

72
00:04:06,173 --> 00:04:09,051
I'm glad to hear there's something
you can't have your way with.

73
00:04:09,134 --> 00:04:10,093
I'm thrilled.

74
00:04:10,177 --> 00:04:11,887
If I can't have him,

75
00:04:11,970 --> 00:04:14,640
it means you have no hope whatsoever.

76
00:04:14,723 --> 00:04:17,601
I'm sure you want things to work out
between me and Hye-jun.

77
00:04:17,684 --> 00:04:18,602
Isn't that right?

78
00:04:20,395 --> 00:04:21,605
I guess you are.

79
00:04:22,731 --> 00:04:25,859
But Jeong-ha won't date just about anyone

80
00:04:25,943 --> 00:04:27,694
even if she and Hye-jun break up.

81
00:04:29,112 --> 00:04:30,405
And I do?

82
00:04:30,489 --> 00:04:32,824
You're so good at insulting others.

83
00:04:32,908 --> 00:04:35,827
Just call the reporter at <i>Out News</i>
and schedule a meeting for me.

84
00:04:43,377 --> 00:04:46,713
Hey, we need another switch
and electrical outlet over here.

85
00:04:46,797 --> 00:04:49,383
You already told us.
Just go back upstairs.

86
00:04:49,466 --> 00:04:52,761
-Hey, are you here to monitor us?
-Fine. I'm going back upstairs.

87
00:04:54,096 --> 00:04:54,930
Mr. Sa.

88
00:04:55,722 --> 00:04:58,850
-You don't need to give us dinner.
-Were you going to stay for dinner?

89
00:04:58,934 --> 00:05:00,894
-Go up and get some rest.
-Okay.

90
00:05:29,256 --> 00:05:31,216
Looking good.

91
00:05:31,299 --> 00:05:32,175
Come in.

92
00:05:33,593 --> 00:05:35,345
-Hi.
-Yes.

93
00:05:35,429 --> 00:05:36,763
Are you done?

94
00:05:38,306 --> 00:05:40,559
I knew it. He didn't come back upstairs.

95
00:05:40,642 --> 00:05:41,643
What do you mean?

96
00:05:41,727 --> 00:05:44,021
I told him to rest up,
but he must've stepped out.

97
00:05:44,104 --> 00:05:46,565
Why does he need to rest?
Is he not feeling well?

98
00:05:46,648 --> 00:05:49,359
He won't let me tell you guys.

99
00:05:49,443 --> 00:05:51,028
He saw a doctor for his shoulder,

100
00:05:51,111 --> 00:05:54,031
and he was told he'll need
another surgery if he's not careful.

101
00:05:54,114 --> 00:05:55,574
Can you talk to him?

102
00:05:56,158 --> 00:05:58,160
He already had surgery,

103
00:05:58,243 --> 00:06:00,162
but it didn't fully heal.

104
00:06:01,496 --> 00:06:02,414
Can he keep working?

105
00:06:02,497 --> 00:06:05,500
Of course not! But he's being stubborn.

106
00:06:06,626 --> 00:06:08,920
He's too stubborn for his own good.

107
00:06:09,004 --> 00:06:12,049
He takes after his mother,
so he's bullheaded.

108
00:06:12,132 --> 00:06:14,885
I think he's embarrassed to face Hye-jun.

109
00:06:15,552 --> 00:06:17,888
He was against Hye-jun's career choice.

110
00:06:19,806 --> 00:06:21,850
Goodness.

111
00:06:29,399 --> 00:06:30,776
Where have you been?

112
00:06:30,859 --> 00:06:32,861
I was running errands.
Where are you going?

113
00:06:32,944 --> 00:06:36,698
I think I got a job.
I have a meeting at the academy.

114
00:06:37,324 --> 00:06:39,534
-Get going, then.
-What are you up to?

115
00:06:39,618 --> 00:06:42,037
What do you think?
I have to fix up Hye-jun's room.

116
00:06:44,164 --> 00:06:45,999
Can't you give me a ride?

117
00:06:46,083 --> 00:06:49,544
I have to walk all the way down there
to take the bus.

118
00:06:49,628 --> 00:06:51,713
I'm old, so I tire very easily.

119
00:06:51,797 --> 00:06:53,673
You look a lot more energetic than I do.

120
00:06:53,757 --> 00:06:56,093
So? Aren't you going to give me a ride?

121
00:06:56,176 --> 00:06:58,387
I won't. Why should I?

122
00:07:00,597 --> 00:07:04,309
I'd have nothing more to wish for
if you could just talk more nicely.

123
00:07:05,143 --> 00:07:07,896
Then I'd be too perfect.

124
00:07:12,901 --> 00:07:15,779
You're baffled
that you just said that, right?

125
00:07:15,862 --> 00:07:18,824
It's because I started watching
a lot more TV thanks to Hye-jun.

126
00:07:18,907 --> 00:07:21,868
Women love it
when men say stuff like this on TV.

127
00:07:21,952 --> 00:07:25,080
That's because they're good looking.
It won't work if you do it.

128
00:07:25,163 --> 00:07:27,124
Whose fault is it that I look like this?

129
00:07:27,207 --> 00:07:30,085
You gave me nothing good.

130
00:07:30,168 --> 00:07:32,379
-Can I put on some music?
-No, you can't.

131
00:07:43,807 --> 00:07:46,643
Just go alone.
Why do you want me to come with you?

132
00:07:46,726 --> 00:07:48,186
Because it'll bother me.

133
00:07:48,270 --> 00:07:50,939
You'd be so bored
if you had to wait alone outside.

134
00:07:54,776 --> 00:07:56,570
-Is this it?
-Yes.

135
00:07:56,653 --> 00:07:57,821
Come on.

136
00:07:59,614 --> 00:08:00,782
Hello.

137
00:08:00,866 --> 00:08:02,409
You're here.

138
00:08:04,077 --> 00:08:06,037
Did you hire a manager?

139
00:08:06,121 --> 00:08:08,206
No, this is my son.

140
00:08:08,290 --> 00:08:10,709
Oh, I see.

141
00:08:10,792 --> 00:08:12,711
He doesn't resemble you at all.

142
00:08:12,794 --> 00:08:13,879
Take a seat.

143
00:08:13,962 --> 00:08:15,005
Let's sit down.

144
00:08:19,551 --> 00:08:23,013
To be honest, it's still too early
for you to hire a manager.

145
00:08:23,096 --> 00:08:25,515
Unless we work even harder

146
00:08:25,599 --> 00:08:27,893
and bring you more work.

147
00:08:28,602 --> 00:08:30,061
Why did you want to meet?

148
00:08:30,145 --> 00:08:33,064
You got an offer for a TV commercial.
For a health supplement.

149
00:08:33,148 --> 00:08:34,524
Really?

150
00:08:35,150 --> 00:08:36,651
The pay must be pretty good.

151
00:08:36,735 --> 00:08:38,361
Yes, it's for a TV commercial.

152
00:08:38,445 --> 00:08:40,322
It's different from printed ads.

153
00:08:41,323 --> 00:08:44,618
-Would you like something to drink?
-Sure, what do you have?

154
00:08:47,871 --> 00:08:49,748
Well, sir.

155
00:08:49,831 --> 00:08:53,084
Do you mind going down to the first floor
and picking up some beverages?

156
00:08:53,835 --> 00:08:56,421
Why make my son do it?

157
00:08:56,505 --> 00:08:57,923
I don't need to drink anything.

158
00:08:58,006 --> 00:09:00,133
It's nothing difficult.

159
00:09:00,217 --> 00:09:03,053
-What should I get?
-Hey, don't bother.

160
00:09:03,803 --> 00:09:06,806
My gosh.
You must love your son very dearly.

161
00:09:06,890 --> 00:09:08,183
I'll get the staff to do it.

162
00:09:08,266 --> 00:09:11,353
Why make such a fuss?
I can just go pick it up.

163
00:09:11,436 --> 00:09:13,063
Are you complaining that I'm caring?

164
00:09:13,146 --> 00:09:16,233
I'm not complaining.
You're the one making a fuss.

165
00:09:16,316 --> 00:09:18,068
You need to work on this.

166
00:09:18,151 --> 00:09:21,363
Must you talk to me like this
in front of my instructor?

167
00:09:21,446 --> 00:09:23,240
What is she going to think of me now?

168
00:09:23,323 --> 00:09:24,741
And what about our family?

169
00:09:24,824 --> 00:09:26,785
She will think we're a hot mess.

170
00:09:26,868 --> 00:09:29,996
No, I won't. I'll go.

171
00:09:32,499 --> 00:09:35,126
Hold on, ma'am.

172
00:09:37,587 --> 00:09:40,340
Why did I ask you to tag along?
How embarrassing!

173
00:09:40,423 --> 00:09:41,466
Should I leave, then?

174
00:09:42,175 --> 00:09:44,010
No, stay until I'm done.

175
00:09:45,929 --> 00:09:47,389
Goodness.

176
00:09:47,472 --> 00:09:48,848
I'm so embarrassed.

177
00:09:53,979 --> 00:09:58,149
THE FAIRNESS OF SA HYE-JUN'S
BEST ACTOR AWARD QUESTIONED

178
00:10:01,403 --> 00:10:03,613
ISN'T SA HYE-JUN STILL A ROOKIE?

179
00:10:03,697 --> 00:10:05,782
I DON'T GET HOW SOMEONE LIKE HIM
WON THE AWARD

180
00:10:09,869 --> 00:10:11,037
Ae-suk!

181
00:10:15,083 --> 00:10:18,503
-What's wrong?
-I get so angry every time I read these.

182
00:10:18,587 --> 00:10:21,256
People at the broadcasting station
aren't idiots.

183
00:10:21,339 --> 00:10:23,550
They gave him the award
because he deserved it.

184
00:10:23,633 --> 00:10:26,469
Of course!
Hye-jun was the only qualified nominee.

185
00:10:26,553 --> 00:10:28,221
People are still talking about that?

186
00:10:28,305 --> 00:10:30,056
I was reading the malicious comments.

187
00:10:30,140 --> 00:10:31,641
What? Those punks.

188
00:10:33,768 --> 00:10:35,770
I must tell the members.

189
00:10:35,854 --> 00:10:39,983
The Giving Tree, Hye-jun All the Way,
and Sa Hye-jun Gallery.

190
00:10:40,066 --> 00:10:42,819
I'll get the fans together
to raise the funds to sue them.

191
00:10:42,902 --> 00:10:44,863
Is it really necessary to sue them?

192
00:10:44,946 --> 00:10:48,074
Yes. People support that these days.

193
00:10:48,158 --> 00:10:49,617
That's the trend.

194
00:10:49,701 --> 00:10:51,703
Then how come Ms. Lee isn't suing them?

195
00:10:51,786 --> 00:10:54,247
Exactly. We're going to do it
because we're frustrated.

196
00:10:54,331 --> 00:10:56,166
How long is Hye-jun's contract?

197
00:10:56,249 --> 00:10:58,168
-I don't know.
-Find out.

198
00:10:58,251 --> 00:10:59,753
He needs a bigger, better agency.

199
00:10:59,836 --> 00:11:01,713
This agency is no good.

200
00:11:01,796 --> 00:11:03,757
JJamppong? Is it a Chinese restaurant?

201
00:11:05,925 --> 00:11:07,135
What's that?

202
00:11:07,218 --> 00:11:11,139
Oh, I have to drop off
the side dishes at Hae-hyo's place,

203
00:11:11,222 --> 00:11:13,058
so I made some for your family as well.

204
00:11:14,851 --> 00:11:17,604
Great. I was wondering
what I should make for them

205
00:11:17,687 --> 00:11:19,272
when Hye-jun's room is all done.

206
00:11:19,356 --> 00:11:20,607
Is Yeong-nam working too?

207
00:11:20,690 --> 00:11:22,776
-Yes, I think so.
-Ae-suk, Yeong-nam is…

208
00:11:25,403 --> 00:11:26,363
It's nothing.

209
00:11:26,946 --> 00:11:27,822
What is it?

210
00:11:27,906 --> 00:11:30,200
Let's talk later.
I have to go to Hae-hyo's place.

211
00:11:30,283 --> 00:11:32,619
Every time I come here,
I don't want to leave.

212
00:11:33,703 --> 00:11:34,913
Thanks.

213
00:11:34,996 --> 00:11:36,081
I'm off.

214
00:11:45,006 --> 00:11:47,175
-<i>The number you have dialed</i>
-Won Hae-na.

215
00:11:47,258 --> 00:11:48,551
<i>is not available.</i>

216
00:11:48,635 --> 00:11:51,179
-So, is this your plan?
-<i>Please leave a message after the beep.</i>

217
00:11:52,013 --> 00:11:54,140
How much longer

218
00:11:54,224 --> 00:11:56,351
do you think you can avoid seeing
your mother?

219
00:11:58,019 --> 00:12:01,272
MY DAUGHTER

220
00:12:16,996 --> 00:12:19,165
Did you ignore my calls
when you were home?

221
00:12:21,459 --> 00:12:23,753
-I'm sorry.
-Heading out to see Jin-u?

222
00:12:24,754 --> 00:12:26,131
-Yes.
-Before you head out,

223
00:12:26,214 --> 00:12:28,925
can you spare me
about ten minutes of your time?

224
00:12:29,008 --> 00:12:30,885
If you can't, we'll talk later.

225
00:12:32,679 --> 00:12:33,805
I can.

226
00:12:36,224 --> 00:12:38,184
I've done some thinking.

227
00:12:39,644 --> 00:12:41,646
-Are you going to get angry?
-No.

228
00:12:41,729 --> 00:12:44,149
I'm not that close-minded.

229
00:12:44,232 --> 00:12:47,694
You have to be faithful to one man
once you get married,

230
00:12:47,777 --> 00:12:50,405
so I support you dating
as much as you can before that.

231
00:12:50,488 --> 00:12:51,990
-Really?
-Of course,

232
00:12:52,073 --> 00:12:55,618
I'd want to see you dating someone
who I approve of,

233
00:12:55,702 --> 00:12:59,747
but it's okay. I understand
why you're charmed by Jin-u.

234
00:13:00,874 --> 00:13:02,333
Thanks, Mom.

235
00:13:04,043 --> 00:13:05,462
Just don't get pregnant.

236
00:13:06,337 --> 00:13:07,505
And you can't marry him.

237
00:13:09,799 --> 00:13:11,259
Have some fun and come home.

238
00:13:11,342 --> 00:13:13,386
You don't approve at all.

239
00:13:13,470 --> 00:13:16,556
Everything you have belongs to me.

240
00:13:16,639 --> 00:13:18,641
I can claim ownership over you.

241
00:13:18,725 --> 00:13:22,896
Your body is the only thing
you have sole control over.

242
00:13:22,979 --> 00:13:24,731
I never asked you for anything,

243
00:13:24,814 --> 00:13:26,858
so why claim ownership?

244
00:13:26,941 --> 00:13:28,359
I obeyed my parents.

245
00:13:28,443 --> 00:13:30,570
I have to live like that
just because you did?

246
00:13:30,653 --> 00:13:32,071
Yes.

247
00:13:32,155 --> 00:13:33,281
Go meet up with Jin-u.

248
00:13:33,364 --> 00:13:34,866
Have fun with him.

249
00:13:34,949 --> 00:13:37,827
And learn how painful it is
to have a relationship

250
00:13:37,911 --> 00:13:40,246
that has no future.

251
00:13:40,330 --> 00:13:41,998
It'll help you grow.

252
00:13:42,081 --> 00:13:45,126
Mom, you're much scarier than I thought.

253
00:13:45,210 --> 00:13:49,964
I kept giving you guidelines,
and you stayed within them.

254
00:13:50,048 --> 00:13:52,091
That's why we got along so far.

255
00:13:52,175 --> 00:13:53,676
You ruined our relationship.

256
00:13:53,760 --> 00:13:57,806
If it's ruined already
and we can't put it back together,

257
00:13:57,889 --> 00:13:59,599
we should reset it.

258
00:13:59,682 --> 00:14:01,392
-No.
-I don't want to either.

259
00:14:02,852 --> 00:14:06,898
Then I'll have to impose you
with some restrictions.

260
00:14:06,981 --> 00:14:10,568
What kind of restrictions are put in place
when international conflicts occur?

261
00:14:11,528 --> 00:14:13,446
Do you want the credit card or the car?

262
00:14:13,530 --> 00:14:15,365
You're so smart.

263
00:14:16,032 --> 00:14:17,700
Which one will affect you more?

264
00:14:17,784 --> 00:14:19,118
Both, equally.

265
00:14:19,202 --> 00:14:20,745
Don't try to fool me.

266
00:14:20,829 --> 00:14:23,957
I think the credit card
will affect you a lot more.

267
00:14:24,040 --> 00:14:26,668
I'll go easy on you for now.
I'm taking your car away.

268
00:14:28,795 --> 00:14:30,129
Give me your car keys.

269
00:14:40,890 --> 00:14:41,933
All cleared.

270
00:14:42,600 --> 00:14:45,395
Okay, go have fun with your boyfriend.

271
00:14:45,478 --> 00:14:47,188
I'm happy you're dating.

272
00:14:47,272 --> 00:14:49,607
And welcome to the real world.

273
00:14:50,316 --> 00:14:52,527
I didn't think you'd be recording this.

274
00:14:52,610 --> 00:14:55,071
If you want to help,
make it worth your while.

275
00:14:55,154 --> 00:14:57,240
Sure, I want to.

276
00:14:57,323 --> 00:14:59,868
You already know
which law firm you'll be joining, right?

277
00:15:00,577 --> 00:15:01,452
How did you know?

278
00:15:01,536 --> 00:15:03,746
My cousin works
at one of the big law firms.

279
00:15:03,830 --> 00:15:06,249
The elders in our family
always compared us.

280
00:15:07,834 --> 00:15:09,878
Did you date Hye-jun for a long time?

281
00:15:10,545 --> 00:15:12,046
<i>Why is she being so rude?</i>

282
00:15:12,714 --> 00:15:14,966
We were together
all through our early to mid-20s.

283
00:15:15,049 --> 00:15:17,218
I know everything about him
during those years.

284
00:15:17,302 --> 00:15:18,678
Okay, we're ready.

285
00:15:19,345 --> 00:15:22,181
Your love is over,
but you're staying loyal to him.

286
00:15:23,224 --> 00:15:24,851
But is it actually over?

287
00:15:25,476 --> 00:15:27,645
<i>It's none of your business.
I can't stand her.</i>

288
00:15:28,146 --> 00:15:29,772
Should I look at the camera?

289
00:15:29,856 --> 00:15:31,149
Jin-u!

290
00:15:31,649 --> 00:15:33,067
Hae-na!

291
00:15:34,777 --> 00:15:36,404
Didn't your mom find out?

292
00:15:38,239 --> 00:15:41,576
My mom said we can date.

293
00:15:41,659 --> 00:15:44,120
Your mom is amazing.
I was worried for nothing.

294
00:15:46,789 --> 00:15:49,000
We had such a narrow outlook.

295
00:15:49,083 --> 00:15:51,294
My mom is so creative.

296
00:15:52,003 --> 00:15:54,797
For the first time ever,
I realized I would never beat her.

297
00:15:54,881 --> 00:15:57,592
Why beat your mom?
That was never my intention.

298
00:15:57,675 --> 00:16:00,595
Otherwise, I would have never
kept our relationship a secret.

299
00:16:01,888 --> 00:16:03,848
You're a bigger coward than I am.

300
00:16:05,016 --> 00:16:06,809
Yes, I am a coward.

301
00:16:07,602 --> 00:16:10,146
Marriage is reality
whereas dating is like a fantasy.

302
00:16:10,229 --> 00:16:12,690
Going from fantasy to reality…

303
00:16:12,774 --> 00:16:14,233
I don't want to do that.

304
00:16:16,444 --> 00:16:17,946
I see.

305
00:16:19,405 --> 00:16:21,032
I can trust you more now.

306
00:16:21,115 --> 00:16:23,743
Because I now know
you're not recklessly emotional.

307
00:16:24,410 --> 00:16:25,912
It's because I love you.

308
00:16:30,583 --> 00:16:33,044
What? Did that make your heart skip?

309
00:16:33,127 --> 00:16:36,214
-No!
-It clearly did.

310
00:16:37,757 --> 00:16:41,636
What? I'm sure he has a lot
to deal with now. Why is he calling?

311
00:16:42,637 --> 00:16:43,972
Hey, Sa Hye-jun.

312
00:16:44,555 --> 00:16:45,556
How's it going?

313
00:16:46,641 --> 00:16:48,476
<i>Not good. How did you know?</i>

314
00:16:48,559 --> 00:16:51,729
Let's meet. Come to our usual spot.

315
00:16:52,605 --> 00:16:54,524
I'm sorry I've been neglecting you guys.

316
00:17:01,114 --> 00:17:03,908
JJAMPPONG ENTERTAINMENT

317
00:17:14,502 --> 00:17:15,503
Come in.

318
00:17:28,558 --> 00:17:30,101
I'm stepping out for a while.

319
00:17:30,184 --> 00:17:31,894
Call me when you're done.

320
00:17:32,729 --> 00:17:33,980
Okay.

321
00:17:44,699 --> 00:17:45,700
Have a seat.

322
00:17:46,284 --> 00:17:48,661
The office is smaller than I expected.

323
00:17:49,203 --> 00:17:52,832
-You should move to a bigger space.
-This is the right size for us.

324
00:17:55,918 --> 00:17:56,961
Do you want some tea?

325
00:18:05,011 --> 00:18:06,262
I don't want you

326
00:18:07,305 --> 00:18:09,474
to come back into my life.

327
00:18:10,558 --> 00:18:14,645
I always do the opposite of what you want.
And that's how I tested your love.

328
00:18:14,729 --> 00:18:17,857
It took me a while to realize
that was your way of testing me.

329
00:18:18,483 --> 00:18:21,402
And I concluded I couldn't put up
with being tested all the time.

330
00:18:23,780 --> 00:18:25,364
Let's relax around each other now.

331
00:18:26,032 --> 00:18:29,077
Now, I know
that we can't get back together.

332
00:18:30,036 --> 00:18:34,665
And I've also accepted the fact
that we can't even be friends.

333
00:18:36,459 --> 00:18:37,543
Thanks.

334
00:18:39,879 --> 00:18:41,839
I was very happy to see you doing so well.

335
00:18:42,423 --> 00:18:44,509
But I'm the only one who can destroy you.

336
00:18:46,886 --> 00:18:49,472
I cannot allow others to harm you.

337
00:18:50,056 --> 00:18:51,349
So?

338
00:18:52,225 --> 00:18:57,271
Well, I proved
that Sa Hye-jun likes women.

339
00:18:57,897 --> 00:18:59,607
I was happy I could do that for you.

340
00:19:00,566 --> 00:19:02,360
I'm no longer indebted to you.

341
00:19:02,944 --> 00:19:05,029
I didn't know you thought

342
00:19:05,655 --> 00:19:06,864
you were indebted to me.

343
00:19:12,203 --> 00:19:14,122
I have a heart too.

344
00:19:14,747 --> 00:19:16,833
You seem to think
that I'm a horrible person.

345
00:19:17,625 --> 00:19:20,002
I did many things
to make you think that about me,

346
00:19:20,920 --> 00:19:22,046
but I regret it now.

347
00:19:22,630 --> 00:19:25,049
Back then, I thought
I was being considerate of you.

348
00:19:32,570 --> 00:19:35,406
Your skin turns red
at the slightest touch.

349
00:19:36,157 --> 00:19:39,452
You have combination skin
that is also very sensitive.

350
00:19:40,035 --> 00:19:41,912
The lack of sleep is making it worse.

351
00:19:42,496 --> 00:19:43,998
It's your wedding anniversary.

352
00:19:44,081 --> 00:19:47,585
You're doing a photo shoot,
so I understand why you're nervous.

353
00:19:49,086 --> 00:19:52,548
I'll apply some calming cream first.

354
00:20:02,183 --> 00:20:04,894
I love this one-client setup.

355
00:20:04,977 --> 00:20:06,479
I feel like a princess.

356
00:20:07,229 --> 00:20:08,606
Please visit us often.

357
00:20:08,689 --> 00:20:11,358
I hope you don't become too famous

358
00:20:11,442 --> 00:20:12,693
so this can be my secret.

359
00:20:13,486 --> 00:20:16,071
Thank you. I'll take that as a compliment.

360
00:20:20,034 --> 00:20:22,953
HAE-HYO

361
00:20:24,038 --> 00:20:28,083
1.1 MILLION FOLLOWERS

362
00:20:31,337 --> 00:20:33,255
You look very comfortable.

363
00:20:34,173 --> 00:20:35,841
Is this your office?

364
00:20:37,051 --> 00:20:39,220
No, it's not.

365
00:20:39,720 --> 00:20:42,306
But you pay all the expenses
with the money that I earn.

366
00:20:42,389 --> 00:20:45,142
<i>That prick is trying to take credit
for everything again.</i>

367
00:20:48,604 --> 00:20:50,815
-It's just so odd.
-What?

368
00:20:50,898 --> 00:20:53,651
Hae-hyo's follower count. It's too high.

369
00:20:53,734 --> 00:20:55,569
It's none of your business.

370
00:20:55,653 --> 00:20:57,905
I tend to pry
when I'm fixated on something.

371
00:20:58,531 --> 00:21:02,034
If he'd hired one of those companies
like you said, then I'd understand.

372
00:21:02,117 --> 00:21:06,455
Okay, let's say he did.
But why is that any of your business?

373
00:21:06,539 --> 00:21:08,123
He's too perfect.

374
00:21:09,375 --> 00:21:13,254
That comfortable, well-off vibe he exudes
bothers me.

375
00:21:14,004 --> 00:21:16,507
As you know,
my self-esteem has hit rock bottom.

376
00:21:16,590 --> 00:21:18,884
I'll feel much better
if he turns out to be someone

377
00:21:18,968 --> 00:21:20,803
who resorts to such tricks to get ahead.

378
00:21:20,886 --> 00:21:23,264
"Rich people are not all that different."

379
00:21:23,889 --> 00:21:27,810
In that sense, I guess popularity is fair.

380
00:21:27,893 --> 00:21:29,562
It's not something you can buy.

381
00:21:29,645 --> 00:21:31,647
My gut tells me that he did it.

382
00:21:41,198 --> 00:21:43,742
Oh, you're still here.

383
00:21:44,994 --> 00:21:47,079
<i>Gosh, Won Hae-na…</i>

384
00:21:47,705 --> 00:21:49,623
I'll put the side dishes in the fridge.

385
00:21:49,707 --> 00:21:52,668
Please let me know what to make next.

386
00:21:53,669 --> 00:21:55,337
<i>I must tell her to quit.</i>

387
00:21:58,966 --> 00:22:01,218
Jin-u's mother is a good cook.

388
00:22:01,302 --> 00:22:03,137
It's seasoned perfectly.

389
00:22:03,220 --> 00:22:04,888
And it tastes light and clean.

390
00:22:05,472 --> 00:22:08,434
That's why I'm putting up with a lot.

391
00:22:08,517 --> 00:22:10,060
Just so you can eat good food.

392
00:22:10,144 --> 00:22:12,771
Thank you so very much.
Keep on putting up with her, then.

393
00:22:17,526 --> 00:22:19,194
Where's the list?

394
00:22:19,778 --> 00:22:21,739
<i>I have to tell her to quit.</i>

395
00:22:22,781 --> 00:22:26,160
What's in season now? I don't have
much of an appetite these days.

396
00:22:27,870 --> 00:22:28,954
Well…

397
00:22:29,038 --> 00:22:31,999
How about something spicy?
<i>Deodeok</i> seasoned with gochujang.

398
00:22:34,001 --> 00:22:36,253
Don't use gochujang.

399
00:22:36,337 --> 00:22:38,380
Grill it with some sweet rice flour.

400
00:22:40,174 --> 00:22:43,552
Why don't you make it here?
It's best when it's fresh.

401
00:22:43,636 --> 00:22:46,263
-What about braised semi-dried pollock?
-I'd love that!

402
00:22:47,431 --> 00:22:51,060
<i>What? You can't tell her to quit
because of these side dishes?</i>

403
00:22:51,560 --> 00:22:53,312
I make really good braised monkfish.

404
00:22:53,395 --> 00:22:55,939
My gosh!
Now, I'm craving braised monkfish.

405
00:22:56,815 --> 00:22:58,400
I'll make some for you.

406
00:22:58,484 --> 00:23:01,820
Delicious food
is the best remedy for stress.

407
00:23:03,197 --> 00:23:04,323
Why would I be stressed?

408
00:23:04,406 --> 00:23:05,366
You're not?

409
00:23:05,449 --> 00:23:07,368
No, I'm not.

410
00:23:07,451 --> 00:23:10,579
You're too quick to make assumptions.

411
00:23:10,663 --> 00:23:12,623
Bad press is better than no press.

412
00:23:12,706 --> 00:23:15,292
No one talks about Hae-hyo,
so I thought you'd be upset.

413
00:23:15,376 --> 00:23:17,211
No, it's the opposite.

414
00:23:17,294 --> 00:23:20,589
Also, stop comparing Hae-hyo with Hye-jun.

415
00:23:20,673 --> 00:23:23,258
Hae-hyo can do something else
if this doesn't work out.

416
00:23:23,342 --> 00:23:24,385
He has many options.

417
00:23:24,468 --> 00:23:27,054
"Option"? What is that?

418
00:23:27,763 --> 00:23:30,224
I mean, he has many choices.

419
00:23:30,307 --> 00:23:33,310
I see. You could've worded it like that
in the first place.

420
00:23:33,394 --> 00:23:36,146
I didn't understand what you meant.
I should use that word.

421
00:23:36,230 --> 00:23:38,065
Anyway, take care.

422
00:23:41,652 --> 00:23:42,653
<i>I must tell her.</i>

423
00:23:44,321 --> 00:23:45,406
Don't come back.

424
00:23:49,910 --> 00:23:51,036
I've said it.

425
00:23:51,120 --> 00:23:53,580
It's her fault for not hearing me
and coming back.

426
00:24:00,796 --> 00:24:02,631
I guess you're not that busy.

427
00:24:04,299 --> 00:24:06,218
I told her, and she wants to meet you.

428
00:24:06,301 --> 00:24:07,928
That actress I mentioned.

429
00:24:08,637 --> 00:24:10,139
Thanks. Who is it?

430
00:24:11,849 --> 00:24:13,851
-I'll give you her number.
-My gosh.

431
00:24:15,519 --> 00:24:17,646
This big brother always does
something for you.

432
00:24:17,730 --> 00:24:20,065
But look at you.
Even now, I made time to come here.

433
00:24:20,149 --> 00:24:22,985
And what? "I guess you're not that busy"?

434
00:24:23,068 --> 00:24:26,864
I'm not sorry anymore.
I want to tease you again.

435
00:24:26,947 --> 00:24:30,033
-"Big brother"? When's your birthday?
-September 27. When's yours?

436
00:24:30,117 --> 00:24:31,577
November 4.

437
00:24:31,660 --> 00:24:33,203
Hi, big bro.

438
00:24:33,287 --> 00:24:34,329
Hey, don't do that.

439
00:24:35,080 --> 00:24:36,123
Jeez.

440
00:24:37,332 --> 00:24:38,876
-Let's go eat.
-I have to go home.

441
00:24:38,959 --> 00:24:41,545
Why do you always say that
when you see me?

442
00:24:41,628 --> 00:24:42,921
Why today of all days?

443
00:24:43,005 --> 00:24:45,132
I have to get ready for my live broadcast.

444
00:24:45,215 --> 00:24:47,676
Are you going to be a YouTuber today?

445
00:24:47,760 --> 00:24:49,511
You don't even have many subscribers.

446
00:24:49,595 --> 00:24:52,806
It's because I'm not focusing on it,
and I don't plan to.

447
00:24:52,890 --> 00:24:56,935
I'm just going to treat it as my diary
and use it to communicate with others.

448
00:24:58,353 --> 00:25:00,147
What will you talk about today?

449
00:25:00,814 --> 00:25:02,357
Watch it later if you're curious.

450
00:25:08,405 --> 00:25:10,908
Did you see Hye-jun?

451
00:25:13,035 --> 00:25:15,579
I did, but I'm not happy.

452
00:25:15,662 --> 00:25:18,332
He's neglecting his friends
because of his girlfriend.

453
00:25:19,917 --> 00:25:21,376
Way to go, Hye-jun.

454
00:25:24,254 --> 00:25:25,756
When did you see him?

455
00:25:27,424 --> 00:25:28,967
I've just been texting him.

456
00:25:29,593 --> 00:25:33,096
I know he's busy and tired,
so I don't want to ask him to meet up.

457
00:25:33,180 --> 00:25:35,349
And I don't want to ask him
about the rumors.

458
00:25:35,432 --> 00:25:38,101
Why can't you?
You said your relationship is solid.

459
00:25:39,895 --> 00:25:42,356
I'm just waiting for him to tell me first.

460
00:25:42,439 --> 00:25:45,275
I was never good at waiting,
but I've changed.

461
00:25:48,612 --> 00:25:49,947
I guess you love him.

462
00:25:50,447 --> 00:25:52,115
That's what love does to you.

463
00:25:52,199 --> 00:25:54,159
You begin to like things you couldn't do.

464
00:25:56,495 --> 00:25:59,081
Why are you single
when you know so much about love?

465
00:25:59,164 --> 00:26:00,082
You're so naive.

466
00:26:01,583 --> 00:26:03,836
Let's go. I'll give you a ride.

467
00:26:03,919 --> 00:26:06,004
It's Hye-jun's job, but I'll do it.

468
00:26:06,088 --> 00:26:07,881
I'd never make him do it.

469
00:26:07,965 --> 00:26:09,466
I'd just tell him to go home and rest.

470
00:26:12,135 --> 00:26:13,262
Hurry up.

471
00:26:13,345 --> 00:26:14,346
Okay.

472
00:26:17,099 --> 00:26:18,308
-Cheers!
-Cheers!

473
00:26:25,607 --> 00:26:26,525
It's so refreshing.

474
00:26:27,651 --> 00:26:29,653
It's been so long since I last drank.

475
00:26:29,736 --> 00:26:31,905
You've been working too hard.

476
00:26:31,989 --> 00:26:34,491
Are you a workaholic now?
You never take a break.

477
00:26:34,575 --> 00:26:36,285
Working relaxes me.

478
00:26:37,202 --> 00:26:39,288
I want to work a lot while I'm in my 20s.

479
00:26:39,371 --> 00:26:40,747
Right.

480
00:26:40,831 --> 00:26:43,333
After we serve in the military
and turn 30,

481
00:26:43,417 --> 00:26:44,960
things will be different.

482
00:26:45,502 --> 00:26:48,463
Gosh, the military. When should I enlist?

483
00:26:49,006 --> 00:26:52,509
Hey, you have to postpone it
as much as you can.

484
00:26:52,593 --> 00:26:54,052
Work while you can.

485
00:26:54,136 --> 00:26:56,972
Your next show… Yes, <i>The First Human</i>!

486
00:26:57,472 --> 00:26:58,724
That's one grand title.

487
00:27:00,100 --> 00:27:02,936
You'll see Hae-hyo often
because you're both in it.

488
00:27:03,729 --> 00:27:05,689
I was excited to work with him,

489
00:27:07,357 --> 00:27:09,484
but he snapped at me earlier.

490
00:27:09,568 --> 00:27:10,861
I'm sure you did too.

491
00:27:10,944 --> 00:27:12,571
Right, I did.

492
00:27:13,822 --> 00:27:15,657
It's nice having childhood friends.

493
00:27:16,742 --> 00:27:17,993
Why did you snap at him?

494
00:27:18,869 --> 00:27:20,078
Because of Ji-a's interview.

495
00:27:21,830 --> 00:27:24,416
But what if

496
00:27:26,960 --> 00:27:28,503
Jeong-ha sees that interview?

497
00:27:36,762 --> 00:27:38,055
Why are you following me?

498
00:27:39,723 --> 00:27:41,308
I don't want to talk to you.

499
00:27:41,892 --> 00:27:44,686
I'm going to keep trying to talk to you.

500
00:27:44,770 --> 00:27:45,979
Did you see this?

501
00:27:46,063 --> 00:27:48,357
It's an exclusive interview with Ji-a.

502
00:27:48,440 --> 00:27:50,609
EXCLUSIVE INTERVIEW
WITH SA HYE-JUN'S EX-GIRLFRIEND

503
00:27:50,692 --> 00:27:53,570
I guess Hye-jun really is popular.
An exclusive at this hour?

504
00:27:53,654 --> 00:27:55,948
I know. What were you up to?

505
00:27:56,782 --> 00:27:58,575
