I was just worried.

756
00:45:49,673 --> 00:45:51,216
Min-jae is my agent.

757
00:45:51,300 --> 00:45:53,594
She believed in me when I had nothing,

758
00:45:53,677 --> 00:45:55,638
and she works hard to keep me motivated.

759
00:45:55,721 --> 00:45:56,972
I'm not arguing with it.

760
00:45:57,056 --> 00:45:59,058
Let me be the person who talks to her.

761
00:46:00,142 --> 00:46:01,769
I don't want to hurt her.

762
00:46:02,519 --> 00:46:03,979
<i>Treat me like that, too.</i>

763
00:46:05,898 --> 00:46:07,024
Okay.

764
00:46:14,490 --> 00:46:16,951
Gosh. He sounds like the CEO of an agency.

765
00:46:18,077 --> 00:46:20,287
Why can't I argue with him?

766
00:46:20,996 --> 00:46:21,956
Why not?

767
00:46:22,581 --> 00:46:23,582
Why can't I?

768
00:46:24,333 --> 00:46:25,292
Why is that?

769
00:46:26,001 --> 00:46:27,211
Gosh.

770
00:46:32,132 --> 00:46:33,008
Ma'am.

771
00:46:34,468 --> 00:46:36,220
Goodness, it's been a while, Hae-hyo.

772
00:46:36,720 --> 00:46:39,348
You're so busy that
I don't get to see you when I come.

773
00:46:39,431 --> 00:46:41,433
I heard you're in a series with Hye-jun.

774
00:46:41,517 --> 00:46:45,145
Yes. He has the leading role,
and I have the supporting role.

775
00:46:45,229 --> 00:46:47,022
It doesn't matter who has the lead.

776
00:46:47,106 --> 00:46:48,190
Only the roles matter.

777
00:46:48,273 --> 00:46:51,068
Looking at Hye-jun,
fame really does happen overnight.

778
00:46:51,151 --> 00:46:53,153
He woke up one day to find himself famous.

779
00:46:53,988 --> 00:46:55,906
That can happen to you, too.

780
00:46:56,699 --> 00:46:57,658
Thank you.

781
00:46:58,617 --> 00:46:59,785
Where is my mom?

782
00:46:59,868 --> 00:47:01,578
She went out. She's meeting someone.

783
00:47:02,413 --> 00:47:05,332
But she didn't seem excited
about the meeting.

784
00:47:12,006 --> 00:47:13,007
Stop.

785
00:47:15,634 --> 00:47:17,094
I don't want to eat with you.

786
00:47:17,720 --> 00:47:19,680
Why must we talk over a meal?

787
00:47:20,556 --> 00:47:24,309
You know, I never forget
to give credit where credit's due.

788
00:47:24,810 --> 00:47:27,104
Ms. Kim, thanks to you,

789
00:47:27,187 --> 00:47:30,733
I met Mr. Yoon and got a big return.
I ought to show my appreciation.

790
00:47:31,775 --> 00:47:34,028
If you truly mean that,
don't pick and choose.

791
00:47:34,111 --> 00:47:35,988
You must be honest with every situation.

792
00:47:36,655 --> 00:47:39,992
Park Do-ha was the one
who got Hae-hyo in <i>Catch</i>.

793
00:47:40,701 --> 00:47:42,327
I am very offended.

794
00:47:42,828 --> 00:47:44,204
Why did you lie to me?

795
00:47:44,288 --> 00:47:46,790
I won't be making
any more introductions to you.

796
00:47:47,374 --> 00:47:49,918
It was only a friendly prank
to get close to you,

797
00:47:50,002 --> 00:47:52,337
so I can't believe
you took me for my word.

798
00:47:52,421 --> 00:47:54,882
Life is full of deceptions.

799
00:47:54,965 --> 00:47:57,634
People only realize it
when they're the victims.

800
00:47:57,718 --> 00:48:01,305
Hae-hyo has an extremely high number
of followers on social media.

801
00:48:03,098 --> 00:48:04,391
<i>What is he getting at?</i>

802
00:48:06,060 --> 00:48:08,979
What does him
being popular on social media have

803
00:48:09,063 --> 00:48:10,314
anything to do with this?

804
00:48:10,397 --> 00:48:12,066
You know how that's possible.

805
00:48:12,775 --> 00:48:15,235
I've bought them with money before too.

806
00:48:16,195 --> 00:48:18,614
Quite simple, isn't it?
It only takes a few clicks.

807
00:48:22,576 --> 00:48:23,577
<i>As if I'd admit to it.</i>

808
00:48:24,161 --> 00:48:25,996
How should I know if it's simple or not?

809
00:48:26,747 --> 00:48:28,665
I agreed to meet you

810
00:48:28,749 --> 00:48:31,752
only because I'm a decent human being
even though I didn't want to.

811
00:48:32,377 --> 00:48:35,506
-Our relationship ends here.
-No can do.

812
00:48:36,590 --> 00:48:37,966
I'll be good, I-yeong.

813
00:48:38,634 --> 00:48:39,843
What did you call me?

814
00:48:39,927 --> 00:48:42,179
You're too young and pretty
to be called "ma'am."

815
00:48:42,262 --> 00:48:44,348
Who'd guess that you're Hae-hyo's mom?

816
00:48:44,848 --> 00:48:46,892
You think I'm some pushover, don't you?

817
00:48:47,684 --> 00:48:50,729
If you thought you could
laugh things over with me,

818
00:48:50,813 --> 00:48:53,107
I urge you to reconsider. Re-evaluate.

819
00:48:54,066 --> 00:48:55,526
Got it.

820
00:48:55,609 --> 00:48:59,404
I'll re-evaluate my situation
and do my best to get on your good side.

821
00:49:06,870 --> 00:49:09,164
After the interview,
you're needed in Gangnam.

822
00:49:09,248 --> 00:49:10,457
What do you want to eat?

823
00:49:10,999 --> 00:49:12,501
Something light.

824
00:49:12,584 --> 00:49:14,378
A sandwich and melon smoothie then.

825
00:49:14,920 --> 00:49:16,463
<i>Today, I'm here with Sa Hye-jun,</i>

826
00:49:16,547 --> 00:49:19,133
one of the hottest actors
that's been trending.

827
00:49:19,216 --> 00:49:22,553
Can you greet the viewers
of <i>Memory Talk Talk</i>?

828
00:49:23,554 --> 00:49:25,389
Hello, I'm actor Sa Hye-jun.

829
00:49:25,472 --> 00:49:29,143
This is your first interview following
your Best Actor Award last year.

830
00:49:29,226 --> 00:49:30,060
Right.

831
00:49:30,144 --> 00:49:33,105
Aren't you here to promote
your new series <i>The First Human</i>?

832
00:49:33,188 --> 00:49:34,356
I am.

833
00:49:34,439 --> 00:49:37,151
<i>The First Human</i> deals with
the power struggle and romance

834
00:49:37,234 --> 00:49:39,319
of young adults born
into prestigious families.

835
00:49:39,903 --> 00:49:42,614
You're known for your dreamy gazes.

836
00:49:42,698 --> 00:49:45,075
I'm curious about how you'll portray

837
00:49:45,159 --> 00:49:47,995
the romance between you
and your partner Jin Seo-u.

838
00:49:48,078 --> 00:49:49,121
How will it be?

839
00:49:49,204 --> 00:49:50,455
It's too early to say,

840
00:49:50,539 --> 00:49:52,541
but I'm curious
about our chemistry as well

841
00:49:52,624 --> 00:49:54,877
since we used to model together.

842
00:50:57,522 --> 00:50:58,607
Don't come any closer.

843
00:51:03,445 --> 00:51:04,529
We…

844
00:51:05,489 --> 00:51:06,323
broke up.

845
00:51:07,658 --> 00:51:08,700
Did you forget that?

846
00:51:22,256 --> 00:51:23,298
I knew it.

847
00:51:24,967 --> 00:51:26,218
You can't live without me.

848
00:51:39,815 --> 00:51:42,484
<i>Cut.</i> We'll take a short break.

849
00:51:45,237 --> 00:51:47,948
It sure is awkward
to do scenes like this with you.

850
00:51:48,490 --> 00:51:49,950
"You can't live without me."

851
00:51:50,450 --> 00:51:52,035
-Stop it.
-Stop what?

852
00:51:52,661 --> 00:51:54,121
You haven't changed at all.

853
00:51:54,621 --> 00:51:55,872
Likewise.

854
00:51:58,375 --> 00:52:00,752
-You're glistening a bit.
-I had to dance, remember?

855
00:52:01,253 --> 00:52:03,922
My regular makeup artist
took her maternity leave.

856
00:52:04,006 --> 00:52:05,924
Someone new took over,

857
00:52:06,008 --> 00:52:07,676
but she's not considerate enough.

858
00:52:08,260 --> 00:52:11,388
Then can I introduce you
to a makeup artist

859
00:52:11,471 --> 00:52:14,182
who is skilled with her hands
and warm at heart?

860
00:52:16,935 --> 00:52:18,729
Are you vouching for your girlfriend?

861
00:52:19,396 --> 00:52:20,731
-How did you know?
-A hunch.

862
00:52:24,526 --> 00:52:26,320
-Give me her number then.
-Sure.

863
00:52:26,903 --> 00:52:29,781
-I guess you'll need your phone.
-I have it memorized.

864
00:52:30,365 --> 00:52:31,992
Well, hello, lover boy.

865
00:52:37,247 --> 00:52:38,415
Are you filming tomorrow?

866
00:52:38,498 --> 00:52:40,500
-I'll be at it with Hae-hyo.
-Hae-hyo?

867
00:52:41,126 --> 00:52:43,920
Oh, right.
Won't it get physical between you two?

868
00:52:44,004 --> 00:52:45,756
I'll be beating him up.

869
00:52:45,839 --> 00:52:47,841
I'd love to come by and watch.

870
00:52:47,924 --> 00:52:49,634
-You should.
-Can I?

871
00:52:50,802 --> 00:52:52,429
But won't you lose in a fight?

872
00:52:52,512 --> 00:52:54,806
What? Why do you always say that?

873
00:53:00,729 --> 00:53:02,522
Aren't you exhausted?

874
00:53:02,606 --> 00:53:04,399
Even on a tight schedule,

875
00:53:04,483 --> 00:53:06,526
your face keeps glowing.

876
00:53:07,194 --> 00:53:08,445
Maybe it's the red ginseng.

877
00:53:09,404 --> 00:53:11,656
You were born this way, Mr. Workaholic.

878
00:53:12,783 --> 00:53:15,327
He's heading overseas
for his fan meet-up event tomorrow.

879
00:53:15,911 --> 00:53:18,663
-So?
-You called him a workaholic,

880
00:53:18,747 --> 00:53:20,540
so I thought I'd recite his schedule.

881
00:53:20,624 --> 00:53:22,292
I'm filming later at night too.

882
00:53:22,376 --> 00:53:24,294
I thought I'd recite my schedule too.

883
00:53:24,378 --> 00:53:25,379
It feels good to say it.

884
00:53:27,923 --> 00:53:30,092
Can you stop eating? You'll gain weight.

885
00:53:33,845 --> 00:53:35,931
-How about slicked back hair?
-Yes, let's.

886
00:53:44,314 --> 00:53:46,358
-We need to get going.
-Sure.

887
00:54:00,914 --> 00:54:02,165
<i>Gyeoksejigam</i> is the word.

888
00:54:02,249 --> 00:54:03,750
What does that mean?

889
00:54:05,252 --> 00:54:08,463
Being astonished
at how much things have changed.

890
00:54:09,339 --> 00:54:11,675
It's used in situations where

891
00:54:11,758 --> 00:54:14,845
you feel like decades have passed
because the change is too drastic.

892
00:54:15,929 --> 00:54:17,597
Yes, that's the one.

893
00:54:18,432 --> 00:54:20,851
-You weren't sure?
-I knew the gist of it.

894
00:54:22,102 --> 00:54:23,353
He sure has made it big.

895
00:54:24,146 --> 00:54:25,814
The sight of him is blinding now.

896
00:54:29,067 --> 00:54:30,735
Filming will begin in ten minutes!

897
00:54:31,403 --> 00:54:32,737
Got it.

898
00:54:33,488 --> 00:54:35,657
-He needs to get going.
-I'm almost done.

899
00:54:39,536 --> 00:54:40,662
Hye-jun.

900
00:54:44,541 --> 00:54:45,584
Hey, Hae-hyo.

901
00:54:46,835 --> 00:54:49,796
-You made your big brother come to you.
-You're the younger one.

902
00:54:49,880 --> 00:54:52,591
Jeong-ha came with me today.
She's the only help I have.

903
00:54:53,633 --> 00:54:54,885
Hi.

904
00:54:55,927 --> 00:54:56,803
Hi.

905
00:54:58,472 --> 00:54:59,848
Hi, Jeong-ha.

906
00:54:59,931 --> 00:55:02,601
-Oh, hey.
-I've been doing well in your place.

907
00:55:03,477 --> 00:55:04,644
I see. Is that so?

908
00:55:05,645 --> 00:55:06,897
Well, let's get going.

909
00:55:12,152 --> 00:55:14,321
Jeong-ha, could we talk?

910
00:55:23,872 --> 00:55:26,625
Were you shocked
to see Yeong-jin in your place?

911
00:55:27,792 --> 00:55:29,878
Hye-jun didn't ask me
for today's shooting,

912
00:55:29,961 --> 00:55:31,379
so I figured.

913
00:55:32,631 --> 00:55:35,383
Too many eyes are on Hye-jun now
for you to do

914
00:55:35,467 --> 00:55:36,843
both his and Hae-hyo's makeup.

915
00:55:37,761 --> 00:55:39,221
Of course.

916
00:55:39,304 --> 00:55:41,389
I was going to call you to set things up,

917
00:55:41,932 --> 00:55:44,476
but you had Hae-hyo to care for too,

918
00:55:44,559 --> 00:55:45,602
so I didn't.

919
00:55:45,685 --> 00:55:46,978
I thought I'd tell you today.

920
00:55:47,729 --> 00:55:48,688
Good thinking.

921
00:55:49,648 --> 00:55:52,108
He has countless events
and people to meet.

922
00:55:52,651 --> 00:55:54,819
On top of that, being in this TV series

923
00:55:55,403 --> 00:55:57,239
requires a makeup artist on standby.

924
00:55:57,322 --> 00:55:58,782
It's why I had her promoted.

925
00:55:59,407 --> 00:56:01,326
You'll be best as an observer right now.

926
00:56:02,410 --> 00:56:03,370
Got it.

927
00:56:05,247 --> 00:56:07,457
Managing his schedule
sure is tough enough.

928
00:56:10,085 --> 00:56:11,503
REPORTER KIM SU-MAN

929
00:56:12,504 --> 00:56:14,005
It's the reporter.

930
00:56:14,089 --> 00:56:15,382
Just a second.

931
00:56:18,718 --> 00:56:20,720
-Yes, Ms. Kim.
-Ms. Lee.

932
00:56:20,804 --> 00:56:22,722
Mr. Sa's dating his makeup artist, right?

933
00:56:25,976 --> 00:56:28,395
What are you talking about? No way.

934
00:56:29,020 --> 00:56:30,605
Haven't you done enough damage?

935
00:56:31,189 --> 00:56:32,983
First the article on Charlie Jung,

936
00:56:33,066 --> 00:56:35,402
and then his ex-girlfriend's interview.

937
00:56:35,485 --> 00:56:37,779
Why can't you leave him alone?

938
00:56:37,862 --> 00:56:40,282
Once again,
you're barking up the wrong tree.

939
00:56:40,365 --> 00:56:42,617
So I'm wrong?

940
00:56:43,952 --> 00:56:47,497
Spread wrongful rumors again
and I'll take action.

941
00:56:47,581 --> 00:56:49,624
Don't you dare write this article.

942
00:56:49,708 --> 00:56:51,418
You do your job

943
00:56:52,502 --> 00:56:53,795
and I'll do mine.

944
00:56:59,593 --> 00:57:00,510
What's going on?

945
00:57:01,887 --> 00:57:03,013
What do we do?

946
00:57:03,555 --> 00:57:05,390
She's going to expose your relationship.

947
00:57:06,308 --> 00:57:08,059
This is bad for Hye-jun.

948
00:57:08,143 --> 00:57:10,061
His image will take a huge blow.

949
00:57:10,145 --> 00:57:12,772
First his ex, now his current girlfriend?

950
00:57:13,523 --> 00:57:15,859
This is bad. It's a terrible sign.

951
00:57:16,359 --> 00:57:18,695
I'm going to sue her ass if she does it!

952
00:57:44,804 --> 00:57:46,181
It's nice to work together.

953
00:57:46,681 --> 00:57:47,849
-Right, Jeong-ha?
-Yes.

954
00:57:48,350 --> 00:57:50,310
Just don't use me as a cover.

955
00:57:50,936 --> 00:57:52,145
Can't you let us?

956
00:57:53,063 --> 00:57:54,105
Okay, fine.

957
00:57:54,689 --> 00:57:57,067
-Hey.
-What are you doing?

958
00:57:57,150 --> 00:57:59,736
It'll only be believable
if she's by my side.

959
00:58:00,403 --> 00:58:01,613
Is that so?

960
00:58:03,448 --> 00:58:04,366
Yes, it is.

961
00:58:04,449 --> 00:58:07,118
Besides, her standing with me
doesn't make her mine.

962
00:58:08,036 --> 00:58:10,121
You two always claim ownership over things

963
00:58:10,205 --> 00:58:11,414
that aren't even yours.

964
00:58:16,920 --> 00:58:17,963
It's Seo-u. Take it.

965
00:58:20,799 --> 00:58:22,717
-Hey.
-Hi, brothers.

966
00:58:23,218 --> 00:58:25,637
It's too bad we don't
have any scenes together.

967
00:58:25,720 --> 00:58:27,013
Are you filming today?

968
00:58:27,097 --> 00:58:28,640
No, I'm here to practice.

969
00:58:28,723 --> 00:58:31,101
Isn't it weird to be romantic with him?

970
00:58:31,184 --> 00:58:34,771
Why would it be
when we're dating? Didn't you know that?

971
00:58:34,854 --> 00:58:37,482
-Hey.
-<i>What's with the sour-face?</i>

972
00:58:37,565 --> 00:58:41,236
<i>That's just how I'll be thinking
while filming this series.</i>

973
00:58:41,820 --> 00:58:43,405
I can't afford this one to tank.

974
00:58:43,989 --> 00:58:46,032
-We should grab a bite sometime.
-<i>Sure.</i>

975
00:58:46,116 --> 00:58:48,910
Bye, Hae-hyo. Be nice to my boyfriend.

976
00:58:48,994 --> 00:58:49,911
<i>Bye!</i>

977
00:58:52,205 --> 00:58:53,456
What's with her?

978
00:58:54,290 --> 00:58:56,167
She's being true to her character.

979
00:58:56,835 --> 00:58:58,128
The show should be a hit.

980
00:59:00,755 --> 00:59:02,465
We film the next scene in five.

981
00:59:02,549 --> 00:59:04,092
-Sure.
-Got it.

982
00:59:15,311 --> 00:59:17,147
Can you take a photo of us?

983
00:59:17,230 --> 00:59:18,982
-Why?
-To savor the moment.

984
00:59:38,501 --> 00:59:41,671
Don't you have a job out of town tomorrow?
Let me drive you there.

985
00:59:41,755 --> 00:59:43,590
It's okay. I can take the bus.

986
00:59:46,259 --> 00:59:47,927
Hye-jun's busy tomorrow morning,

987
00:59:48,762 --> 00:59:50,847
and he'll head abroad
for a fan meet-up event.

988
00:59:52,057 --> 00:59:54,142
-I didn't ask.
-I'm just saying.

989
01:00:02,025 --> 01:00:04,736
ALARM 5:00 A.M.

990
01:00:50,949 --> 01:00:52,992
HYE-JUN

991
01:00:54,619 --> 01:00:58,206
<i>You, who I have by my side,
are always the best.</i>

992
01:01:01,918 --> 01:01:04,003
<i>"Out of sight, out of mind."</i>

993
01:01:05,213 --> 01:01:07,757
<i>Not being within eyesight
makes someone grow distant.</i>

994
01:01:09,050 --> 01:01:11,010
<i>I had faith
that our relationship was solid.</i>

995
01:01:12,220 --> 01:01:13,596
<i>But faith</i>

996
01:01:14,180 --> 01:01:15,932
<i>is much more fragile than love.</i>

997
01:01:20,687 --> 01:01:22,730
-Hi.
-Over here.

998
01:01:27,735 --> 01:01:30,196
-Are you the assistant director?
-Yes, I am.

999
01:01:30,280 --> 01:01:32,448
I'm here as Kim Song-yeon's makeup team.

1000
01:01:32,532 --> 01:01:34,742
-You're Su-cheol's friend, right?
-Yes.

1001
01:01:34,826 --> 01:01:36,161
She's in that van.

1002
01:01:36,244 --> 01:01:37,620
-Thank you.
-Thanks.

1003
01:01:39,998 --> 01:01:42,041
That wasn't what happened.

1004
01:01:42,542 --> 01:01:45,003
Come on. Let's start over.

1005
01:02:02,687 --> 01:02:04,230
Unbelievable.

1006
01:02:04,981 --> 01:02:06,816
It's almost midnight, damn it.

1007
01:02:08,067 --> 01:02:10,778
Could you lift your chin a bit?

1008
01:02:11,362 --> 01:02:14,782
Sure. Why can't they just be done with it?

1009
01:02:18,036 --> 01:02:20,955
I'm really sorry to ask,
but can you face straight ahead?

1010
01:02:21,039 --> 01:02:24,626
Don't try to be perfect
and be a little less dense.

1011
01:02:26,419 --> 01:02:30,089
The makeup around your lips,
nose, and cheeks have gotten flaky.

1012
01:02:32,008 --> 01:02:33,593
Are you patronizing me?

1013
01:02:33,676 --> 01:02:36,888
It may not seem like a big deal,
but it'll show on the screen.

1014
01:02:38,389 --> 01:02:39,641
Fine, just make it quick.

1015
01:02:41,309 --> 01:02:42,435
Are you done?

1016
01:02:48,191 --> 01:02:49,692
Be careful what you wish for.

1017
01:02:51,319 --> 01:02:53,363
So much for Mr. Workaholic.

1018
01:02:53,988 --> 01:02:55,531
Wake me up at the airport.

1019
01:02:56,950 --> 01:02:58,034
We're here.

1020
01:03:22,934 --> 01:03:24,352
<i>But why do you hate rainy days?</i>

1021
01:03:25,186 --> 01:03:27,188
<i>It makes me feel like I'm all alone.</i>

1022
01:03:27,981 --> 01:03:29,941
<i>I'll call you when it rains.</i>

1023
01:03:30,817 --> 01:03:32,193
<i>You're not alone.</i>

1024
01:03:43,788 --> 01:03:46,499
HYE-JUN

1025
01:03:55,300 --> 01:03:57,635
CALLING

1026
01:06:09,976 --> 01:06:10,935
You can come in.

1027
01:06:59,435 --> 01:07:06,716
Subtitle translation by: Hye-lim Park

1028
01:07:30,335 --> 01:07:33,272
RECORD OF YOUTH

1029
01:07:34,435 --> 01:07:36,479
<i>She has an interview with Hae-ji
for a makeup job today.</i>

1030
01:07:36,562 --> 01:07:38,064
<i>Are you sleeping?</i>

1031
01:07:38,147 --> 01:07:40,066
Now we have scandals round-the-clock.

1032
01:07:40,149 --> 01:07:41,526
<i>What do you think people want to know?</i>

1033
01:07:41,609 --> 01:07:45,404
-It's who he used to date.
-He seemed to be really competent.

1034
01:07:45,488 --> 01:07:47,365
Stay away from my family.

1035
01:07:47,448 --> 01:07:50,576
Did you know that you can pay
to increase the number of followers?

1036
01:07:50,660 --> 01:07:52,495
I wanted to prove
that I could make it on my own.

1037
01:07:52,578 --> 01:07:54,372
That's the one thing I asked you
to let me have!

1038
01:07:54,455 --> 01:07:55,289
What's this?

1039
01:07:55,373 --> 01:07:57,708
I want to make it up to you
for having been a lousy father.

1040
01:07:57,792 --> 01:08:00,002
Why did you call Hae-hyo first and not me?

